<br>
It reminds me of the joke tour of heaven where the catholics were partying and the baptists were dancing and all the christians were in there own special, seperate area and God said &quot;SHhhhhhhh, tiptoe... they think that they are the only ones here.&quot; <p><img src="http://www.sonic.net/knightstribunal/images/ravlow.jpg" border="0">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubranamileq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branamileq</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/13/01 9:27:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=240>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fucking Jesusfreaks</span><hr size=1> To say I know nothing of other religions is not true.  I know the basic beliefs of the other major religions, judaism, catholicism, islam, buddhism.  And I DO believe that the feeling I was talking about earlier is unique to christianity.  For example, buddhists and muslims practice a very strict religion.  Such as days or weeks of meditation, and having to kneel and pray towards the sun every day or something along those lines.  The difference between that and christianity is, you wont be &quot;cursed&quot; if you dont do a certain thing, or if you do something wrong, because every sin (except one) is forgivable.. nothing you do is going to condemn you for eternity, as long as you believe Jesus.  unlike islams who.. are seen as heretics if they don't visit meccha once in their lifetimes to walk in a big circle around a monolith??? ya.. that makes sense.<br>
<br>
And if followers of these other religions are just as convinced of their own religion, why are there no Buddhist or Hindu missionaries coming to america to show us the light?  But there are thousands of christian missionaries going to india etc..  I feel lucky to have grown up with christianity.  If I grew up in India, I would probably practice hinduism like my parents..  but Im sure I would hear about christianity in my lifetime.  and I remember a bible verse saying that he wont &quot;judge&quot; anyone who hasnt heard the message of christianity.  So, if a hindu practices it his whole life but never heard about christianity, he wont burn in hell.  but once he is introduced to christianity, he has a choice to accept it or reject it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=130.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.show